# LMS Islam Fakultas — Project Rules

You are working on **LMS Islam Fakultas**, a Learning Management System built with Laravel 13 + React/Inertia.

## Architecture

### Tech Stack
- **Backend:** Laravel 13 (PHP 8.3+)
- **Frontend:** React 19 + Inertia.js 3 + Tailwind CSS 4 + shadcn/ui (Radix UI)
- **Build:** Vite 7 + `@vitejs/plugin-react` + `@tailwindcss/vite`
- **Database:** MySQL
- **Auth:** Laravel built-in session auth (not Sanctum/Sanctum API)
- **Icons:** lucide-react
- **Animation:** framer-motion

### Directory Structure
```
app/
├── Http/
│   └── Controllers/
│       ├── Admin/        # Admin role controllers
│       ├── Instructor/   # Instructor role controllers
│       ├── Student/      # Student role controllers
│       ├── Auth/         # Auth controllers
│       └── *.php         # Shared controllers (DiscussionController, etc.)
├── Models/               # Eloquent models
├── Providers/
├── Livewire/             # (if any Livewire components)
resources/
├── js/
│   ├── Components/       # Shared React components
│   ├── Pages/            # Inertia page components
│   │   ├── Admin/
│   │   ├── Instructor/
│   │   ├── Student/
│   │   └── Auth/
│   └── Layouts/          # Layout components
├── css/app.css           # Tailwind entry
routes/
├── web.php               # Main web routes
└── console.php           # Artisan commands
```

### Role-Based Structure
The app has **3 roles**: `admin`, `instructor`, `student`
- Each role has separate controllers under `App\Http\Controllers\{Role}\`
- Each role has separate Inertia pages under `resources/js/Pages/{Role}/`
- Role-based dashboard route: `{role}.dashboard`
- Middleware checks `auth()->user()->role` to determine routing

### Models (app/Models/)
- **User** — extends Authenticatable, has role enum (admin/instructor/student)
- **Course** — belongs to User (instructor)
- **Module** — belongs to Course
- **Material** — belongs to Module
- **Content** — belongs to Material
- **ContentProgress** — belongs to User + Content (tracks student progress)
- **Assignment** — belongs to Module
- **Submission** — belongs to Student + Assignment
- **Quiz** — belongs to Module
- **QuizQuestion** — belongs to Quiz
- **QuizAttempt** — belongs to Student + Quiz
- **Discussion** — morphTo userable, belongsTo course
- **Enrollment** — belongs to User (student) + Course
- **Certificate** — belongs to User (student) + Course

## Naming Conventions

### PHP / Laravel
- **Controllers:** PascalCase, suffix with `Controller`, group by role directory
- **Models:** Singular PascalCase (Course, Module, ContentProgress)
- **Migrations:** snake_case with timestamp prefix
- **Routes:** kebab-case URLs, dot-notation route names (e.g., `admin.courses.index`)
- **Validation:** Form Request classes in `app/Http/Requests/`

### React / Inertia
- **Components:** PascalCase, one component per file
- **Pages:** PascalCase, match route structure (e.g., `Admin/Courses/Index.jsx`)
- **Hooks:** camelCase with `use` prefix
- **Props:** camelCase in JavaScript, snake_case in PHP (Inertia auto-converts)
- Use `class-variance-authority` (cva) + `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` for class management
- Import shadcn components from `@/Components/ui/`

### Inertia Patterns
- Server-side: `Inertia::render('Role/PageName', [...])` from controllers
- Client-side: `router.get/post/put/delete()` for navigation
- Shared data via `HandleInertiaRequests` middleware
- Flash messages: `session('success')` / `session('error')`

## Commands

### Development
```bash
# Run dev servers (Vite + Artisan serve + queue + logs)
npm run dev          # Uses concurrently

# Run tests
php artisan test

# Clear cache
php artisan optimize:clear

### Queue Worker
```bash
php artisan queue:listen --tries=1 --timeout=0
```

### Database
```bash
php artisan migrate
php artisan migrate:fresh --seed
php artisan db:seed
```

## Coding Standards

### PHP
- Strict types: `declare(strict_types=1)` on all new files
- Use constructor property promotion where possible
- Type hint everything (return types, parameter types)
- Use Laravel facades sparingly; prefer dependency injection
- Use Form Requests for validation in any significant endpoint
- Eloquent: use `with()` for eager loading, avoid N+1 queries

### React
- Functional components with hooks (no class components)
- Inertia form handling: use `useForm` or `useFormWithFileUpload` helper
- State management: local state + Inertia shared data (avoid Redux/Zustand)
- Use shadcn/ui components (Dialog, Sheet, Form, Table, Button, etc.)
- Tailwind CSS 4 syntax (no @apply for one-off styles)

### Database
- Migrations should be reversible (use `down()` method)
- Foreign keys with cascade on delete where appropriate
- Use enums for fixed-value columns (role, status, type)
- Index frequently queried columns

## Important Gotchas
- **Cloudflare Tunnel:** App behind Cloudflare — must use [`URL::forceScheme('https')` and `trustProxies(at: '*')`] for assets
- **Vite should run:** Frontend assets served via Vite; after changes run `npm run build`
- **Queue needed:** Some features use queue (notifications, certificate generation)
- No API routes yet — all routes are web-based (Inertia)
- User passwords are hashed with Bcrypt (Laravel default)
- Session storage in MySQL (not file/database)
- Environment file at `/var/www/laravel/.env`, production mode
